 ('1178', 'Alcatel', 'Alcatel Flash 2', null, 5.0, null, null, null, null, '2015-09-22 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '720 x  1280', 294, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 3000, 25.0, 600.0, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/Alcatel/Alcatel Flash 2.jpg', 'The Alcatel Flash 2 sports a 5-inch display with 720 x 1280 pixels, and is powered by a 64-bit, octa-core MediaTek MTK6753 processor clocked at 1.3 GHz. Other features: LTE connectivity, dual SIM support, 2 GB of RAM, 16 GB of storage space, microSD card support, and a 3000 mAh battery.'),
 ('1179', 'Alcatel', 'Alcatel Flash 3', null, 4.6, null, null, null, null, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 479, null, 13.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, null, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', '/images/nothumb_phone_235x235.jpg', 'The Alcatel Flash 3 is expected to come with a 4.6-inch display with a 1080 x 1920 FHD screen. Under the hood is the MediaTek Helio X20 MT6797 SoC, it features a deca-core 2.3GHz CPU with the Mali-T880 GPU. The Alcatel Flash 3 will carry 3GB of RAM with 32GB of internal storage inside. On the back of the phone is a 13MP camera, with an 8MP snapper in front to take selfies and handle video chats. Android 6.0.1 is pre-installed.'),
