 ('1488', 'Alcatel', 'Alcatel Tru', null, 5.0, 156, 141.0, 71.5, 9.9, '2016-08-15 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0)', '480 x  854', 196, null, 5.0, 2.0, 1.0, 8.0, 2000, 14.0, 400.0, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/Alcatel/Alcatel Tru.jpg', 'The Alcatel Tru sports a 5-inch screen with 480 x 854 pixels, thus offering one of the least sharp displays currently on the market. The phone is powered by a not-so-powerful quad-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 210 CPU clocked at 1.1 GHz, further offering 1 GB of RAM, 8 GB of expandable storage space, and a 2000 mAh battery for "all day use." There''s a 2 MP camera on the front of the handset, and a 5 MP one on the back - with LED flash and "Polaroid filters". The new Alcatel smartphone features a "soft noir faux leather back", and unfortunately runs Android Lollipop.'),
 ('1489', 'Alcatel', 'Alcatel U5', null, 5.0, null, 140.7, 71.8, 9.95, '2017-02-26 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '480 x  854', 196, null, 5.0, 2.0, 1.0, 8.0, 2050, null, null, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/Alcatel/Alcatel U5.jpg', 'The Alcatel U5 sports a 5-inch display, quad-core processor, 1 GB of RAM, 8 GB internal storage and a slot for microSD. There is a 5-megapixels camera on the back and a 2-megapixels front snapper. The phone is LTE enabled and runs Android 6.0 Marshmallow.'),
