 ('1491', 'Amazon', 'Amazon Fire HD 10', 260, 10.1, 482, 262.0, 159.0, 7.7, '2015-09-17 00:00:00', 'Tablet', 'Android (5.0), Fire OS 5 UI', '1280 x  800', 149, 'IPS LCD', 5.0, null, 1.0, 32.0, null, null, null, 'Yes', 'Wi-Fi positioning', 'manufacturer/Amazon/Amazon Fire HD 10.jpg', 'The Amazon Fire HD 10 features a 10.1-inch IPS display with a resolution of 800x1280 pixels up front, while a 1.5GHz quad-core chipset and 1GB of RAM will make up the performance part. You can take pictures with the 5MP rear camera. There is 32GB of storage. Fortunately, you can boost the memory prowess of the Amazon Fire by throwing in a microSD card inside, which can be up to 128GB in size. You also get unlimited cloud storage for Amazon content. The Amazon Fire runs forked Android that is known as Fire OS5 Bellini and comes with none of Google''s services or apps aboard.'),
