 ('1617', 'Asus', 'Asus FonePad 7 FE170CG', null, 7.0, 482, 192.0, 110.0, 10.7, '2014-05-24 00:00:00', 'Tablet', 'Android (4.3)', '600 x  1024', 170, 'IPS LCD', 2.0, 0.3, 1.0, 8.0, null, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/Asus/Asus FonePad 7 FE170CG.jpg', 'The Asus FonePad 7 (model number FE170CG) features 7-inch IPS display with 600 x 1024 pixels, dual-core 1.2GHz Intel Atom Z2520 processor, VGA front-facing camera, 2MP rear camera, 1GB of RAM and 8GB of expandable internal memory.'),
 ('1618', 'Asus', 'Asus Fonepad 7 FE375CL', null, 7.0, 482, 194.3, 108.9, 9.8, null, 'Tablet', 'Android (5.0)', '800 x  1280', 216, 'IPS LCD', 5.0, 2.0, 2.0, 16.0, null, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/Asus/Asus Fonepad 7 FE375CL.jpg', 'While the new Fonepad doesn''t look too different from the Fonepad 7 FE170CG that was released in 2014, it brings important improvements when it comes to specs. The device is powered by a quad-core Intel Atom Z3530 processor clocked at 1.3 GHz, and sports a 7-inch IPS display with 800 x 1200 pixels. It obviously lets you make phone calls, supporting micro SIM cards, LTE, and 3G connectivity. Furthermore, the Fonepad 7 features a 2 MP front-facing camera, 5 MP rear camera, 2 GB of RAM, 8 GB or 16 GB of internal memory, 5 GB of cloud storage space (for life), and microSD card slot.'),
 ('1619', 'Asus', 'Asus Fonepad 7 ME372CG', null, 7.0, 482, 196.8, 120.0, 10.5, '2013-09-06 00:00:00', 'Tablet', 'Android (4.2)', '800 x  1280', 216, 'IPS LCD', 5.0, 1.2, 1.0, 8.0, 3950, null, null, '3.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/Asus/Asus Fonepad 7 ME372CG.jpg', 'The FonePad 7 has all the marks of an affordable device - it sports a 7-inch display with a resoultion of 1280 x 800 pixels and runs on an Intel Z2560 1.6GHz chip. Good news is Android here is in its almost latest version, 4.2 Jelly Bean. The camera is a 5-megapixel rear one and there’s a 1.2MP front shooter. The battery is capable of running for 10 hours on a single charge, and that’s awesome. The device also sports cellular connectivity.'),
 ('1620', 'Asus', 'Asus Fonepad 8', null, 8.0, 482, 214.0, 120.0, 8.9, null, 'Tablet', 'Android (4.4)', '800 x  1280', 189, 'IPS LCD', 5.0, 2.0, 2.0, 16.0, null, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/Asus/Asus Fonepad 8.jpg', 'The Asus Fonepad 8 is an 8-inch tablet powered by a 1.8-GHz quad-core Intel Atom Z3560 processor. Its other features include a 5-megapixel camera, stereo speakers, 1GB of RAM and 8GB of storage.'),
 ('1621', 'Asus', 'Asus Fonepad Note 6', null, 6.0, 482, 164.8, 88.8, 10.3, null, 'Tablet', 'Android (4.4, 4.2.2)', '1080 x  1920', 367, 'Super IPS+ LCD', 8.0, 1.2, 2.0, 16.0, null, 23.0, 490.0, '3.0, EDR', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/Asus/Asus Fonepad Note 6.jpg', 'The Asus FonePad Note sports a 6" Full HD display, a stylus, and is powered by a dual-core 2 GHz Intel Atom Z2560 processor. Other specs include 2 GB of RAM, 8 MP camera on the back and dual front stereo speakers. There''s also a longish stylus tucked in a silo here, and the Asus phablet sports HSPA+ radio, which will allow you to talk on GSM networks and download stuff with speeds up to 42Mbit/s'),
 ('1622', 'Asus', 'Asus Fonepad', null, 7.0, 482, 196.4, 120.1, 10.4, '2013-02-25 00:00:00', 'Tablet', 'Android (4.1)', '1280 x  800', 216, 'IPS LCD', 3.0, 1.2, 1.0, 16.0, 4270, null, null, '3.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/Asus/Asus Fonepad.jpg', 'Asus Fonepad is an affordable 7" Android Jelly Bean tablet with 3G voice and mobile data that place a smartphone in it. The kinky thing about the slate is that it is not powered by an ARM processor, but the new Intel Atom Z2420 with full Android compatibility and good balance of performance and energy efficiency, that allows up to nine hours of battery life during hardware-accelerated 1080p Full HD video decoding. \nIt has a front 1.2-megapixel camera for easy video chat and ASUS SonicMaster audio technology with MaxxAudio 3 processing by Waves ensures clear, well-rounded sound quality.\nThe 7" screen features 1280 x 800 HD resolution for crisp, and its IPS technology ensures nice colors with 178-degree wide viewing angles, and sufficient outdoor brightness.'),
 ('1623', 'Asus', 'Asus M530w', null, 2.4, 156, 117.0, 65.0, 13.8, null, 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Standard (6.0)', '320 x  240', 167, 'TFT', 2.0, null, 0.06, null, 1200, 5.0, 200.0, '2.0', null, 'manufacturer/Asus/Asus M530w.jpg', 'The Asus M530w is a tri-band GSM plus 3G, WM6 Standard phone. It features 2.4-inch QVGA display, 2-megapixel camera, QWERTY keyboard, microSD slot and WiFi. It is powered by 416 MHz processor and has 64MB RAM and 256MB ROM.'),
