 ('2578', 'HTC', 'HTC HD7S', 500, 4.3, 156, 122.0, 68.0, 11.2, '2011-03-21 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Phone, 7.5 Mango', '480 x  800', 217, 'S-LCD', 5.0, null, 0.6, 16.0, 1230, 4.5, 276.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC HD7S.jpg', 'HTC HD7S is a re-branded version of the HTC HD7. The phone is equipped with a 4.3-inch WVGA Super LCD display which is the largest in the WP7 lineup, but even more intriguing is the fact that the phone will ship with an updated version of Microsoft''s platform supporting copy and paste. On the hardware side you get a 1GHz single-core processor, while in the camera department you have a 5-megapixel snapper.'),
 ('2579', 'HTC', 'HTC HD7', 200, 4.3, 156, 122.0, 68.0, 11.2, '2010-10-11 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Phone, 7.5 Mango', '480 x  800', 217, 'LCD', 5.0, null, 0.6, 16.0, 1230, 6.33, 310.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC HD7.jpg', 'HTC HD7 is a high-end Windows Phone 7 device powered by 1GHz processor. It also features a 4.3" capacitive touch display, 5MP camera with flash, Wi-Fi and A-GPS.'),
 ('2580', 'HTC', 'HTC Harrier', null, 0.0, 156, 125.0, 69.8, 18.7, null, 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Professional (2003)', '240 x  320', null, 'TFT', 0.3, null, 0.1, null, 1490, 4.0, 168.0, null, null, 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Harrier.jpg', 'The Audiovox XV-6600 (HTC Harrier) is CDMA Pocket PC smartphone and features EV-DO high speed data (some models), Bluetooth, full extractable QWERTY keyboard, and 400 Mhz Intel processor with 128 Mb ram. Versions with and without camera are available.'),
 ('2581', 'HTC', 'HTC Hero CDMA', null, 3.2, 156, 113.0, 56.0, 14.0, '2009-09-03 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.1)', '320 x  480', 180, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.3, null, 1500, 4.0, null, '2.0, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Hero CDMA.jpg', 'The HTC Hero for Sprint will not be just a CDMA version of the best Android handset we have used this far. It will have a new design, lacking the famous chin, which was so distinctive for HTC’s Android products. Some of the most important features coming with the Hero include, of course, the colourful Sense UI, a 5MP camera, 3.5mm jack, GPS, stereo Bluetooth, Wi-Fi and 3G.'),
 ('2582', 'HTC', 'HTC Hero S', null, 4.0, 156, 115.0, 60.0, 12.0, '2011-09-28 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3)', '540 x  960', 275, 'S-LCD', 5.0, 1.3, 0.75, 4.0, 1520, 7.25, 456.0, '3.0', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Hero S.jpg', 'HTC Hero S is an Android 2.3 smartphone with HTC Sense running on top of it. The phone is equipped with a 4 inch Super-LCD qHD display. Rear and front-facing cameras weigh in at 5MP and 1.3MP respectively. Under the hood is a single-core 1.2GHz Qualcomm MSM8655 processor.'),
 ('2583', 'HTC', 'HTC Hero', null, 3.2, 156, 112.0, 56.2, 14.3, '2009-06-24 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.1, 1.5)', '320 x  480', 180, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.3, null, 1350, 7.83, 440.0, '2.0, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Hero.jpg', 'The HTC Hero is the first Android phone of the manufacturer to run the personalized Sense interface. It changes the overall appearance of the OS and adds a number of new features. The Hero is also the first Android phone to support Flash and is powered by a Qualcomm 528MHz processor and 288 MB RAM/512 MB ROM. Additional functionality includes a 3.5mm jack, trackball, GPS, Bluetooth 2.0 and Wi-Fi. It is a quad-band GSM and dual-band 3G handset.'),
 ('2584', 'HTC', 'HTC Himalayas', null, 0.0, 156, 130.0, 70.0, 19.0, null, 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Professional (2003 SE)', '240 x  320', null, 'TFT', 0.3, null, 0.1, null, 1200, 3.5, 130.0, null, null, 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Himalayas.jpg', 'HTC Himalayas is global roaming GSM phone, featuring built-in camera, Bluetooth, polyphonic ringtones, runs on Windows Mobile 2003 for Pocket PC.'),
 ('2585', 'HTC', 'HTC Hurricane', null, 0.0, 156, 108.0, 46.0, 17.5, null, 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Standard (2003 SE)', '240 x  320', null, 'TFT', 1.3, null, 0.06, 0.027, 1150, 3.0, 150.0, '1.2', null, 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Hurricane.jpg', 'HTC Hurricane is a tri-band GSM (900/1800/1900) Smartphone running on Windows Mobile Operating System. It features 1.3-megapixel camera, QVGA screen, and a miniUSB port.'),
 ('2586', 'HTC', 'HTC Imagio', null, 3.6, 156, 117.0, 61.0, 13.0, '2009-10-01 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Professional (6.5)', '480 x  800', 259, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.3, null, 1500, 5.0, 312.0, '2.0, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Imagio.jpg', 'The HTC Imagio is the first smartphone offered by Verizon that runs Windows Mobile 6.5 Professional and also the only one that comes with VCast Mobile TV, powered by Qualcomm''s FLO TV network. Other features include a WVGA screen, GPS, WiFi, a 5-megapixel camera, an accelerometer and TouchFLO user interface.'),
 ('2587', 'HTC', 'HTC Incredible S', 550, 4.0, 156, 120.0, 64.0, 11.7, '2011-02-15 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0.4, 2.3.5, 2.3.3, 2.2)', '480 x  800', 233, 'S-LCD', 8.0, 1.3, 0.75, 1.0, 1450, 9.66, 290.0, '2.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Incredible S.jpg', 'The HTC Incredible S has a 4-inch WVGA Super LCD screen, and a single-core 1GHz Qualcomm 8255 processor, along with 768MB of RAM. What makes it stand out is the fact that the labels of its capacitive buttons are not printed giving the impression of a buttonless device. The buttons also rotate with the screen adding to the overall Android experience. On the rear there is an 8-megapixel camera equipped with dual LED flash and capable of 720p HD video, while the front holds a 1.3-megapixel camera. The phone will also have expandable memory with a microSD slot. The connectivity package is pretty standard: Wi-Fi b/g/n, Bluetooth 2.1 with A2DP and a standard microUSB slot. When it comes to software, the Incredible S will ship with Android Froyo, but HTC promises to swiftly upgrade it to Android Gingerbread.'),
 ('2588', 'HTC', 'HTC Inspire 4G', 450, 4.3, 156, 123.0, 68.0, 12.0, '2011-01-05 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3, 2.2)', '480 x  800', 217, 'S-LCD', 8.0, null, 0.75, 4.0, 1230, 6.0, 372.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Inspire 4G.jpg', 'HTC Inspire 4G is one of the bigger smartphones, with 4.3" screen and a line of capacitive keys below it. We guess it will be very similar to what Europe has in the face of the HTC Desire HD, but with AT&T''s 3G bands. It packs the latest version of HTC''s Sense user interface.'),
 ('2589', 'HTC', 'HTC J', null, 4.3, 156, 131.5, 66.0, 9.5, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0), Sense 4 UI', '540 x  960', 256, null, 8.0, 1.3, 1.0, 16.0, 1810, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC J.jpg', 'HTC J is an Android smartphone with a 4.3" qHD display, 8MP camera, 16GB of internal storage and 1.5GHz processor running the show.'),
 ('2590', 'HTC', 'HTC Jetstream', null, 10.1, 482, 251.0, 178.0, 13.0, '2011-08-31 00:00:00', 'Tablet', 'Android (3.1)', '1280 x  768', 148, 'LCD', 8.0, 1.3, 1.0, 32.0, 7300, null, 900.0, '3.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Jetstream.jpg', 'The HTC Jetstream aka Puccini is a 10.1-inch tablet with Android Honeycomb which is one of the first devices compatible with AT&T''s "true 4G" LTE network, deploying this year.'),
 ('2591', 'HTC', 'HTC Lancaster', null, 2.8, 156, 109.0, 54.0, 17.1, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android', null, null, null, 3.0, null, null, null, 1350, null, null, '2.0', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Lancaster.jpg', 'HTC Lancaster is the first Android-based phone for AT&T. It sports a unique HTC social messaging user interface, full QWERTY keyboard, 2.8" touchscreen, A-GPS and a 3-megapixel camera.\n\n'),
 ('2592', 'HTC', 'HTC Legend American version', null, 3.2, 156, 112.0, 56.3, 11.5, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.1)', '320 x  480', 180, 'AMOLED', 5.0, null, 0.4, null, 1300, 8.16, 440.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Legend American version.jpg', 'This is the American version of HTC Legend. The handset offers a stylish design for users who care how their gadgets look. The Legend is an Android smartphone with a 3.2-inch AMOLED screen and a 5MP camera.'),
