 ('2695', 'HTC', 'HTC Touch Pro', null, 2.8, 156, 102.0, 51.0, 18.0, '2008-06-04 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Professional (6.1)', '480 x  640', 286, 'TFT', 3.2, null, 0.3, null, 1340, 7.0, 367.0, '2.0, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Touch Pro.jpg', 'HTC Touch Pro is the successor of the TyTN II, or a Diamond with a side-sliding QWERTY keyboard. It has similar specs to the latter, including VGA display, WiFi, GPS and 580 MHz Processor.'),
 ('2696', 'HTC', 'HTC Touch Viva', null, 2.8, 156, 104.0, 59.0, 15.7, '2008-09-16 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Professional (6.1)', '240 x  320', 143, 'TFT', 2.0, null, 0.1, null, 1100, 8.0, 270.0, '2.0, EDR', null, 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Touch Viva.jpg', 'The HTC Touch Viva is the budget model in the Touch series, lacking 3G and GPS. It is similar to the original Touch but runs the latest generation TouchFLO 3D interface available also on the Touch HD and Touch 3G.'),
 ('2697', 'HTC', 'HTC Touch2', null, 2.8, 156, 104.0, 55.0, 12.9, '2009-09-02 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Professional (6.5)', '240 x  320', 143, 'TFT', 3.2, null, 0.25, null, 1100, 7.33, 370.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/HTC/HTC Touch2.jpg', 'HTC Touch2 features a 2.8-inch display with resolution of 240x320 pixels, 528MHz Qualcomm 7225 processor, 256MB RAM and 512MB ROM, 3G support, 3.2-megapixel camera, GPS and Windows Mobile 6.5.'),
