 ('3871', 'LG', 'LG Marquee', 100, 4.0, 156, 122.0, 64.0, 9.0, '2011-09-14 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3)', '480 x  800', 233, 'TFT', 5.0, 2.0, 0.5, null, 1500, 5.5, null, '3.0', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Marquee.jpg', 'LG Marquee is a re-branded version of the LG Optimus Black. It features a 1GHz single-core processor, 4-inch ultra-bright NOVA display with WVGA resolution, 512MB RAM, and a five-megapixel camera.'),
 ('3872', 'LG', 'LG Migo', null, 0.0, 156, 82.0, 46.0, 22.0, null, null, null, '96 x  32', null, 'LCD', null, null, null, null, 1000, 3.0, 226.0, null, 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Migo.jpg', 'The LG Migo is a simple CDMA phone designed for kids, so it has a capacity of 4 numbers, with 4 speed-dial keys and an emergency one. It also has vibration and polyphonic ringtones, as well as speakerphone and GPS'),
 ('3873', 'LG', 'LG Mini', null, 3.2, 156, 102.0, 47.5, 10.5, '2010-02-09 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '480 x  854', 306, 'TFT', 5.0, null, null, 0.05, 1000, 7.0, 330.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Mini.jpg', 'The LG Mini GD880 got introduced by the manufacturer as the smallest phone with 3.2-inch display. The handset resembles the LG Pop''s design language, but is slightly more angular. It pack some nice features such as 5MP camera and Wi-Fi, along with some special apps for social networking.'),
