 ('3875', 'LG', 'LG Muziq', null, 2.3, 156, 96.5, 49.0, 15.5, null, null, null, '176 x  220', 125, 'TFT', 1.3, null, null, 0.016, 800, 4.0, 288.0, '1.1', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Muziq.jpg', 'The successor of the Fusic changes the design and replaces the toy-like white color with glossy black surface and VX8600-like keys. It features 262k color TFT display, 1.3 megapixel camera, Bluetooth, Media player, FM radio transmitter and microSD slot for memory.'),
 ('3876', 'LG', 'LG Neon II', 30, 2.4, 156, 103.0, 50.0, 15.0, null, 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  320', 167, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.08, 950, 4.0, 264.0, '2.0, EDR', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Neon II.jpg', 'LG Neon II comes to replace the LG Neon which was released last year for AT&T. The Neon II features a HSDPA connectivity, 2.4" QVGA touch display, QWERTY keyboard, 2MP camera and microSDHC card slot.'),
 ('3877', 'LG', 'LG Neon', null, 2.4, 156, 101.6, 50.8, 16.8, null, null, null, '240 x  320', 167, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, null, 800, 4.0, 250.0, '2.0', null, 'manufacturer/LG/LG Neon.jpg', 'LG Neon is a GSM with side-sliding full QWERTY keyboard featuring a 2.4" LCD touch sensitive display, Bluetooth, MP3 player and microSD(HC) card slot.'),
 ('3878', 'LG', 'LG New Chocolate BL20', null, 2.4, 156, 106.9, 50.8, 12.3, null, 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  320', 167, 'TFT', 5.0, null, null, 0.13, 900, 4.0, 270.0, '2.1, EDR', null, 'manufacturer/LG/LG New Chocolate BL20.jpg', 'The LG New Chocolate BL20 is the new Black Label series slider, sporting a striking red numeric keypad. While details about it are hard to come by for now, it is rumored that this stylish piece of hardware will be equipped with a 5-megapixel camera and a QVGA resolution display. In addition, the keys on the front side seem to be touch-sensitive.'),
 ('3879', 'LG', 'LG New Chocolate BL40G', null, 4.0, 156, 128.0, 51.0, 10.9, '2009-07-07 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '345 x  800', 218, 'TFT', 5.0, null, null, 0.335, 1000, 6.0, 400.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG New Chocolate BL40G.jpg', 'The LG New Chocolate BL40G is identical to the LG BL40, but supports 3G bands suitable for South and North America. It has a 4-inch multitouch-sensitive display with an aspect ratio of 21:9 and scratch-proof glass surface. The sleek body houses an aGPS and Wi-Fi receivers, while the interface is LG''s S-Class 3D.'),
 ('3880', 'LG', 'LG New Chocolate BL40', null, 4.0, 156, 128.0, 51.0, 10.9, '2009-07-07 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '345 x  800', 218, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.25, 1.0, 1000, 6.0, 400.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG New Chocolate BL40.jpg', 'The LG New Chocolate BL40 is the next installment of LG''s Black Label series. It has a 4-inch multitouch-sensitive display with an aspect ratio of 21:9 and scratch-proof glass surface. The sleek body houses an aGPS and Wi-Fi receivers, while the interface is LG''s S-Class 3D.'),
 ('3881', 'LG', 'LG Nitro HD', 250, 4.5, 156, 134.0, 68.0, 10.0, '2011-11-28 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3.5)', '720 x  1280', 326, 'LCD', 8.0, 1.3, 1.0, 4.0, 1830, null, null, '3.0', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Nitro HD.jpg', 'The LG Nitro HD (also known as P930) is an Android 2.3-device with a 1.5GHz dual core processor, 1GB of RAM, an 8-megapixel shooter and a 4.5-inch high resolution display (720x1280 pixels), Wi-Fi, GPS, DLNA, barcode scanner and Bluetooth 3.0 and 4GB of onboard storage.'),
 ('3882', 'LG', 'LG Octane', 350, 0.0, 156, 107.0, 55.0, 16.0, '2010-10-27 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '320 x  240', null, 'TFT', 3.2, null, null, null, null, 6.33, 340.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS, E911', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Octane.jpg', 'The LG Octane has an intriguing form factor – a full QWERTY keyboard, while a small external LCD screen feeds information to you when the handset is closed. The outer LCD display is 176x220 pixels, while the internal one is 240x320 pixels. The LG Octane sports a 3MP camera with flash, and its dimensions are 4.21”x2.16”x0.63”, which is bearable for a landscape QWERTY slider. The keyboard has a navigational D-pad, and LG has decided to go with a non-standard 2.5mm audio jack.'),
 ('3883', 'LG', 'LG Optimus 2X', null, 4.0, 156, 123.9, 63.2, 10.9, '2010-12-16 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0, 2.2)', '480 x  800', 233, 'TFT', 8.0, 1.3, 0.5, 8.0, 1500, 7.83, 400.0, 'Yes', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Optimus 2X.jpg', 'The LG Optimus 2X is the first smartphone to run on a dual-core 1GHz NVIDIA Tegra 2 processor. It has a well-sized display measuring 4 inches, large enough for you to watch the videos you made in HD 1080p. A 1500mAh battery powers the model which will include a microSD slot to expand storage capacity. The device runs Android 2.2 with an upgrade to Android 2.3 expected eventually.'),
 ('3884', 'LG', 'LG Optimus 2', null, 3.2, 156, 113.0, 59.0, 12.0, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3)', '320 x  480', 180, 'TFT', 3.2, null, null, 0.179, 1500, 5.0, 168.0, '3.0', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Optimus 2.jpg', 'The LG Optimus 2 is an Android 2.3 smartphone with a 800 MHz processor, 3.2-megapixel camera, messaging, organizer, microSD card slot and all other features courtesy of the operating system.'),
 ('3885', 'LG', 'LG Optimus 3D MAX', null, 4.3, 156, 126.8, 67.4, 9.6, '2012-02-22 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3.6), Optimus 2.0 Lite UI', '480 x  800', 217, 'IPS LCD', 5.0, 0.3, 1.0, 8.0, 1520, 4.0, 422.0, '3.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Optimus 3D MAX.jpg', 'The Optimus LG 3D Max is the successor to the original Optimus 3D and improves upon the auto-stereoscopic implementation. It has similar, but upgraded specs - a 4.3” WVGA IPS LCD display, dual-core 1.2GHz TI OMAP processor, two 5-megapixel rear cameras, front-facing camera, 802.11 b/g/n Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 3.0, 21Mbps HSPA, NFC, DLNA, and 8GB of internal storage. At 9.6mm, the Optimus 3D Max is slimmer than its predecessor. It will initially run Android 2.3 Gingerbread, but an upgrade to 4.0 ICS is expected.'),
 ('3886', 'LG', 'LG Optimus 3D', null, 4.3, 156, 128.8, 68.0, 11.9, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3, 2.2)', '480 x  800', 217, 'TFT', 5.0, 0.3, 0.5, 8.0, 1500, 4.0, 96.0, '3.0, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Optimus 3D.jpg', 'LG Optimus 3D, is the first 3D capable phone. It has a 4.3" LCD capacitive touchscreen with 480x800 pixels of resolution, with a glasses-free 3D parallax barrier screen technology. The two 5MP cameras on the back of the phone record stereoscopic 3D video at HD resolution, which will probably need some getting used to if you are hoping to get the most out of it, but LG announced partnership with the YouTube 3D channel, which places a dedicated app on the LG Optimus 3D to upload and share the 3D content you have captured with the phone easily. The chipset that makes the stereoscopic imaging possible is the dual-core 1GHz OMAP4 from Texas Instruments.'),
 ('3887', 'LG', 'LG Optimus 4X HD', null, 4.7, 156, 132.4, 68.1, 8.9, '2012-02-23 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.1, 4.0.3), Optimus UI', '720 x  1280', 312, 'IPS LCD', 8.0, 1.3, 1.0, 16.0, 2150, 9.36, 731.0, '4.0', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Optimus 4X HD.jpg', 'LG Optimus 4X HD is an Android 4.0 running smartphone which comes with quad-core NVIDIA Tegra 3 processor, while a 4.7” 1280 x 720 display accompanies its larger than life status – and if that’s not enough, it’s packaged all within a 8.9mm casing. It also features an 8-megapixel rear camera, 1.3-megapixel front-facing snapper, 21Mbps HSPA, 802.11 b/g/n Wi-Fi, 16GB of storage, NFC and Bluetooth 4.0. Worried about the pitfalls with battery drain with this one? Well, the handset packs a hefty 2,150 mAh battery to hopefully give it enough juice to get through a day.'),
 ('3888', 'LG', 'LG Optimus 7Q', null, 3.5, 156, 119.5, 59.5, 15.2, '2010-10-11 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Phone, 7.5 Mango', '480 x  800', 267, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.5, 16.0, 1500, 7.0, 466.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Optimus 7Q.jpg', 'LG Optimus 7Q is a Windows Phone 7 running smartphone featuring a 3.5" touch screen, 5MP camera, Wi-Fi, GPS and 1GHz processor'),
