 ('3984', 'LG', 'LG Spectrum 2', null, 4.7, 156, 134.8, 68.3, 9.2, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0.4)', '720 x  1280', 312, 'IPS LCD', 8.0, 1.3, 1.0, 16.0, 2150, 10.4, 473.0, '4.0', 'A-GPS, S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Spectrum 2.jpg', 'LG Spectrum 2 is equipped with a 4.7 inch True HD IPS screen, which means instead of the oft-criticized PenTile display, the display uses a regular RGB matrix. The rest of the specs look quite enticing as well, including 8-megapixel camera, the dual-core 1.5GHz Qualcomm MSM8960 S4 processor under the hood, NFC support and Android 4.0.4 installed. There is 16GB of native storage and Global radio support (GSM/UMTS/CDMA/LTE).'),
 ('3985', 'LG', 'LG Spectrum', 700, 4.5, 156, 135.0, 69.0, 11.0, '2012-01-09 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0.4, 2.3)', '720 x  1280', 326, 'LCD', 8.0, 1.3, 1.0, 4.0, 1830, 8.3, 348.0, '3.0', 'A-GPS, S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Spectrum.jpg', 'The 4.5" True HD IPS goodness of the LG Spectrum is coming to Verizon with LTE connectivity, and ready to rumble. The latest flagship of the company has the shares specs with the Optimus LTE and the LG Nitro HD for AT&T, mainly since it is the same phone, but with Verizon''s 4G bands. That means we get 4.5" 720x1280 pixels display, 1.5GHz dual-core Snapdragon S3, 1GB RAM, and 8MP camera with 1080p video recording. Unfortunately, it will come with Andorid 2.3 Gingerbread out of the box, until it gets upgraded to Android 4.0 Ice Cream Sandwich.'),
 ('3986', 'LG', 'LG Spirit 4G', null, 4.5, 156, 129.0, 66.0, 9.0, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0)', '540 x  960', 245, 'TFT', 5.0, 1.3, null, 4.3, 2150, 7.0, 200.0, '3.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Spirit 4G.jpg', 'The LG Spirit 4G comes with the Android 4.0 Ice Cream Sandwich platform, a 4.5 inch touchscreen, a 5 MP rear camera and 1.3 MP front shooter, as well as a dual core processor clocked at 1.2 GHz. Of course, it includes all connectivity features native to the platform.'),
 ('3987', 'LG', 'LG Spirit', null, 4.7, null, 133.3, 66.1, 9.9, '2015-02-23 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0)', '720 x  1280', 312, null, 8.0, 1.0, 1.0, 8.0, 2100, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Spirit.jpg', 'The LG Spirit runs Android 5.0 and sports a 4.7-inch HD display, 1.3-GHz quad-core processor, 8-megapixel camera main camera and a 1-megapixel unit on the front, 1GB of RAM, 8GB of storage and LTE connectivity.'),
 ('3988', 'LG', 'LG Splendor', null, 4.3, 156, 125.0, 67.0, 9.0, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0)', '480 x  800', 217, 'IPS LCD', 5.0, 0.3, 0.75, 2.0, 1700, 9.0, 240.0, 'Yes', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Splendor.jpg', 'The LG Splendor sports a classic black square body with silver metal trim. Under the hood it features a 1GHz processor, 768MB of RAM, 4GB of ROM, Adreno 205 GPU, VGA front-facing camera, 5-megapixel rear camera, 1700mAh removable battery, and WVGA display.'),
 ('3989', 'LG', 'LG Spree', null, 4.5, 156, 131.8, 66.8, 8.9, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '480 x  854', 218, 'TFT', 5.0, 2.0, 1.0, 8.0, 1940, 13.0, 234.0, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Spree.jpg', 'On the design and build side, the LG Spree appears to be your typical entry-level handset, offering a polycarbonate construction with a brushed metal finish and large bezels around the display, which is a 4.5-inch (presumably TFT) panel running a resolution of 480 by 854 pixels. The processing work is done by a 1.1GHz quad-core Snapdragon chipset paired with 1GB of RAM. Keeping the lights on is a 1,940 battery. The minimalistic approach that LG adopted with the Spree continues in the imaging department, where the handset is fitted with a 5MP primary camera and a 2MP selfie shooter.'),
 ('3990', 'LG', 'LG Stylo 2 Plus', null, 5.7, 156, 154.9, 79.5, 7.4, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0, 6.0)', '720 x  1280', 258, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2900, 20.12, 460.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Stylo 2 Plus.jpg', 'The LG Stylo 2 Plus has a 5.7-inch In-Cell display that carries a 720 x 1280 resolution, and the Snapdragon 430 chipset is under the hood. That means the phone carries an octa-core 1.4GHz CPU, and the Adreno 505 GPU. 2GB of RAM is inside along with 16GB of internal storage. A 32GB capacity microSD slot is available for those seeking additional memory. A 13MP camera adorns the back of the phone, while a 5MP front-facing snapper shoots selfies and handles video chats. The 2900mAh battery keeps the lights on, and Android 6.0 is pre-installed.'),
 ('3991', 'LG', 'LG Stylo 2 V', null, 5.7, 156, 154.9, 79.5, 7.4, '2016-10-19 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '720 x  1280', 258, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 3000, 13.0, 370.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS, S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Stylo 2 V.jpg', 'Тхе LG Stylo 2 V is a value-priced phablet. The phone features a 5.7-inch screen with a 720 x 1280 resolution and is powered by an octa-core 1.8GHz CPU with 16GB of internal storage inside (8.78GB available to the user). A 2TB capacity microSD slot is available for those needing additional storage. A 13MP rear-facing camera is on board, and a 5MP front-facing camera is available for selfies and video chats.'),
 ('3992', 'LG', 'LG Stylo 2', null, 5.7, 156, 154.9, 79.5, 7.4, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '720 x  1280', 258, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 3000, 25.0, null, '4.1', 'GPS, S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Stylo 2.jpg', 'The LG Stylo 2 sports a 5.7-inch 720p display, a quad-core 1.2 GHz processor (Qualcomm Snapdragon 410), LTE connectivity, 16 GB of expandable storage space, 2 GB of RAM and a 3000 mAh battery. Other features include 13 MP and 5 MP cameras (rear and front) and Android 6.0 Marshmallow.'),
 ('3993', 'LG', 'LG Stylo 3 Plus', null, 5.7, 156, 155.7, 79.8, 7.4, '2017-05-17 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0)', '1080 x  1920', 386, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 32.0, 3080, 14.0, 456.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS, S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Stylo 3 Plus.jpg', 'Running Android 7.0 Nougat out of the box, the LG Stylo 3 Plus replaces the Stylo 2 Plus that T-Mobile launched in 2016. The new handset obviously features a stylus pen, and brings various improvements that make it better than its predecessor. The Stylo 3 Plus is powered by a quad-core Snapdragon 435 processor clocked at 1.4 GHz, further offering a fingerprint scanner, a 13 MP rear camera, 5 MP front-facing camera, 2 GB of RAM, and a 3080 mAh battery.'),
 ('3994', 'LG', 'LG Stylo 3', null, 5.7, 156, 155.7, 80.0, 7.4, '2016-12-22 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0)', '720 x  1280', 258, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 3200, 25.0, null, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS, S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Stylo 3.jpg', 'The LG Stylo 3 offers more bang for the buck than most smartphones in the same price range. First off, the handset runs Android 7.0 Nougat right out of the box.  Also, it comes equipped with a 1.4GHz octa-core processor, coupled with 2GB RAM and 16GB of expandable memory. Moreover, LG Stylo 3 boasts a large 5.7-inch display with HD (720p) resolution, but also a stylus. On the back side, there''s a 13-megapixel camera with LED flash, as well as a fingerprint sensor. A secondary 5-megapixel camera for selfies and video calls is featured on the front side.'),
 ('3995', 'LG', 'LG Stylus 2 Plus', null, 5.7, 156, 155.0, 79.6, 7.4, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 386, 'IPS LCD', 16.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 3000, 7.5, 315.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Stylus 2 Plus.jpg', 'The LG Stylus 2 Plus looks pretty much like the Stylus 2, having the same dimensions and weight: 155 x 79.6 x 7.4 mm and 145 grams. However, the new device comes with many improvements. For example, its 5.7-inch screen is a 1080p one (much sharper than the 720p 5.7-inch display of the regular Stylus 2), while its processor is an unnamed octa-core one clocked at 1.4 GHz. There''s also more RAM available (2 GB, or 3 GB - depending on market), while the rear camera is a 16 MP one. Another notable addition is a fingerprint scanner.'),
 ('3996', 'LG', 'LG Stylus 2', null, 5.7, 156, 155.0, 79.6, 7.4, '2016-02-15 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '720 x  1280', 258, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 1.5, 16.0, 3000, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Stylus 2.jpg', 'The Stylus 2 sports the same 5.7-inch 720p display that we can find on the G Stylo, though it''s thinner (7.4 mm) and lighter (145 grams) than its predecessor. The new handset doesn''t offer too many upgraded features - it''s still got a quad-core 1.2 GHz processor (we assume it''s the Snapdragon 410), LTE connectivity, 16 GB of expandable storage space, and a 3000 mAh battery. There''s a little bit more RAM on the Stylus 2, though (1.5 GB, compared to just 1 GB on the G Stylo), while the cameras have been bumped to 13 MP (rear) and 8 MP (front).'),
