 ('4077', 'LG', 'LG Viper 4G LTE', null, 4.0, 156, 117.0, 62.0, 12.0, '2012-01-09 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0, 2.3)', '480 x  800', 233, 'TFT', 5.0, 0.3, 1.0, 2.0, 1700, 7.0, null, '3.0', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Viper 4G LTE.jpg', 'LG Viper 4G LTE is one of the first LTE enabled smartphones for Sprint, an Android 2.3 Gingerbread handset, equipped with a 1.2GHz dual-core processor, 4" WVGA NOVA screen and 5MP camera.'),
 ('4078', 'LG', 'LG Volt 2', null, 5.0, 156, 139.7, 69.9, 10.2, '2015-06-29 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '720 x  1280', 294, 'IPS LCD', 8.0, 5.0, 1.0, 8.0, 2540, 21.0, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Volt 2.jpg', 'The LG Volt 2 sports a 5-inch IPS display with 720 x 1280 pixels, it''s powered by a quad-core 1.2 GHz processor, and has a 5 MP front-facing camera. Other features include LTE connectivity, an 8 MP rear camera, 1 GB of RAM, 8 GB of expandable internal memory, and a 2540 mAh battery.'),
 ('4079', 'LG', 'LG Volt', null, 4.7, 156, 132.0, 66.0, 10.0, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4)', '540 x  960', 234, 'IPS LCD', 8.0, 1.3, 1.0, 8.0, 3000, 24.0, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Volt.jpg', 'The LG Volt offers Android 4.4 KitKat, a 4.7-inch display with 540 x 960 pixels, quad-core 1.2GHz Snapdragon 400 processor, 1GB of RAM, and 8GB of expandable internal memory. The rear camera is an 8MP one with LED flash.'),
 ('4080', 'LG', 'LG Vortex', 80, 3.2, 156, 114.0, 59.0, 13.0, '2010-11-15 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.2)', '320 x  480', 180, 'LCD', 3.2, null, null, 0.15, 1500, 7.5, 500.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS, S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Vortex.jpg', 'LG Vortex is a device for first-time smartphone users. It sports a healthy-sized 3.2-inch HVGA capacitive touchscreen, GPS, Wi-Fi, 3MP camera, Bluetooth and microSDHC card slot. It is powered by a 600MHz CPU and runs Android 2.2.'),
 ('4081', 'LG', 'LG Voyager', null, 2.8, 156, 118.0, 54.0, 18.0, null, null, null, '400 x  240', 166, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.184, 950, 4.0, 480.0, '1.2', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Voyager.jpg', 'The LG Voyager VX10000 (VX10k) is the successor of the enV VX9900, upgrading it with huge (additional) external touch-sensitive display with 240x400 pixels resolution and only three hardware keys on the front, reminding of the LG PRADA. It is a clamshell that opens in landscape orientation to reveal another big landscape internal display (again 400x240), stereo speakers and QWERTY for messaging. The Voyager supports MediaFlo for Verizon VCast MobileTV service.'),
 ('4082', 'LG', 'LG Vu Plus', null, 3.0, 156, 109.0, 53.0, 15.0, '2010-05-24 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  400', 155, 'TFT', 3.0, null, null, 0.05, 950, 3.0, 288.0, '2.0, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Vu Plus.jpg', 'LG Vu Plus comes as the successor of LG Vu. The phone now offers users the convenience of a physical QWERTY keyboard on top of its touchscreen. Just like the original LG Vu, it''ll offer AT&T''s FLO TV service which enables customers to catch up on some of their favorite media content on its capacitive display. In addition, the LG Vu Plus features a 3” capacitive touchscreen, 7.2Mbps HSDPA, 3-megapixel auto-focus camera, microSD card support, and 50MB of internal storage.'),
 ('4083', 'LG', 'LG Vu', null, 3.0, 156, 108.0, 55.0, 13.0, '2008-04-01 00:00:00', null, null, '240 x  400', 155, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.12, 1000, 3.0, 250.0, '1.2', null, 'manufacturer/LG/LG Vu.jpg', 'LG Vu has Prada-like design: it is half-inch slim candybar with 3" 240x400 pixels touch sensitive display. It uses the same UI as the Prada and Viewty phones and has similar functionality, but only 2-megapixel camera. It will be available in two variants: CU920 with Mobile TV using MediaFlo, CU915 without TV.'),
 ('4084', 'LG', 'LG Wine 4', null, 3.0, 156, 111.8, 53.3, 15.2, null, 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  400', 155, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.25, 0.5, 900, 6.0, 360.0, '3.0', null, 'manufacturer/LG/LG Wine 4.jpg', 'The LG Wine 4 is a simple clamshell phone with a 3-inch WQVGA screen, 5-megapixel camera, 512 MB of storage and a microSD card slot.'),
 ('4085', 'LG', 'LG Wine III', null, 3.0, 156, 111.0, 52.0, 16.0, null, 'Basic phone', null, '240 x  400', 155, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.26, 900, 5.5, 280.0, '3.0', 'S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Wine III.jpg', 'The LG Wine III is a basic clamshell phone that offers a 3'''' main display, a secondary monochrome screen, microSD card slot, 2 MP camera, and Bluetooth 3.0.'),
 ('4086', 'LG', 'LG Wine II', 50, 2.4, 156, 101.0, 50.0, 16.0, null, null, null, '240 x  320', 167, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.256, 900, 3.16, 336.0, '2.1, EDR', 'S-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Wine II.jpg', 'LG Wine II UN430 is the successor of LG Wine, upgrading it with EVDO data and 2MP camera. Other features include stereo bluetooth, microSDHC card slot and organizer.'),
 ('4087', 'LG', 'LG X Mach', null, 5.5, 156, 149.1, 76.5, 8.9, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1440 x  2560', 538, 'IPS LCD', 12.3, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 3000, 13.0, 300.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG X Mach.jpg', 'The LG X Mach features 5.5-inch QHD display, 1.8GHz hexa-core processor, 3GB of RAM and 32GB of internal storage. There is 12.3 megapixel camera on the back, as well as 8 megapixel front shooter. The phone is powered by 3000mAh battery.'),
 ('4088', 'LG', 'LG X Power (International)', null, 5.3, 156, 148.9, 74.9, 7.9, '2016-06-16 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '720 x  1280', 277, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 4100, 8.0, 200.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/LG/LG X Power (International).jpg', 'The LG X Power won''t win any hardware spec contests with its 5.3-inch screen at a mere 1280 x 720 resolution, nor its 2GB of RAM, 16GB of internal storage, or quad-core MediaTek processor. But we can''t deny that LG picked an appropriate phone to call the X Power this time around, giving the phone a good-sized 4,100 mAh battery.'),
 ('4089', 'LG', 'LG X Power', null, 5.3, 156, 148.9, 74.9, 7.9, '2016-06-16 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '720 x  1280', 277, 'IPS LCD', 8.0, 5.0, 1.5, 16.0, 4100, 40.0, 935.0, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/LG/LG X Power.jpg', 'The LG X Power won''t win any hardware spec contests with its 5.3-inch screen at a mere 1280 x 720 resolution, nor its 1.5GB of RAM, 16GB of internal storage, or quad-core Qualcomm processor. But we can''t deny that LG picked an appropriate phone to call the X Power this time around, giving the phone a good-sized 4,100 mAh battery.'),
 ('4090', 'LG', 'LG X calibur', null, 0.0, null, null, null, null, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 4100, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', '/images/nothumb_phone_235x235.jpg', 'The LG X calibur is expected to be a rugged, dust- and water-resistant (IP68) phone with a 4100 mAh battery.'),
 ('4091', 'LG', 'LG X cam', null, 5.2, 156, 147.5, 73.6, 6.9, '2016-02-15 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2500, 5.66, 260.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG X cam.jpg', 'The LG X cam features a 5.2-inch screen, carrying a 1080 x 1920 resolution. An octa-core 1.14GHz CPU powers the phone. 2GB of RAM is inside, along with 16GB of native storage. This model sports two rear-facing cameras. One is 13MP while the other is 5MP. A front-facing 8MP camera takes selfies and handles video chats. A 2520mAh battery keeps the lights on, and Android 6.0 is pre-installed. The LG X cam is extremely light, weighing only 118 grams, and has an "elegant curved finish on the front." The handset''s thickness ranges from 5.2mm to 6.9mm. It will be offered in Titan Silver, White, Gold and Pink Gold.'),
 ('4092', 'LG', 'LG X power 2', null, 5.5, 156, 154.7, 78.1, 8.4, '2017-02-23 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0)', '720 x  1280', 267, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 4500, null, null, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG X power 2.jpg', 'Running Android 7 Nougat, the LG X power 2 features LTE connectivity, a 1.5 GHz octa-core processor, 16 GB of expandable storage space, and 2 GB of RAM (or 1.5 GB in some markets). As for cameras, the handset has a 13 MP rear one, and a 5 MP front facing one, both with LED flashes.'),
 ('4093', 'LG', 'LG X screen', null, 4.9, 156, 142.6, 71.8, 7.1, '2016-02-15 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '720 x  1280', 298, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2300, 9.0, 120.0, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG X screen.jpg', 'The LG X screen features a 4.93-inch In-cell main screen with a 720 x 1280 HD resolution. A 1.76-inch secondary screen is on top and shows notifications, time, weather and battery status without having to turn on the phone. Users will be also able to access their favorite apps from the screen. This is similar to the secondary screen found on the LG V10. A quad-core 1.2GHz CPU drives the model, which features 2GB of RAM and 16GB of native storage. Keeping the generator humming is a 2300mAh battery, and Android 6.0 is pre-installed. This model will be offered in Black, White and Pink Gold.'),
 ('4094', 'LG', 'LG X venture', null, 5.2, 156, 154.0, 75.8, 9.29, '2017-05-22 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0)', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'IPS LCD', 16.0, 5.0, 2.0, 32.0, 4100, 24.0, 730.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG X venture.jpg', 'The LG X venture is built around a metal frame, offering what AT&T calls a "non-slip design". The new LG phone is IP68-certified for dust- and water-resistance, so it should be able to survive under water up to 1.5 meters for 30 minutes. Furthermore, the handset complies with the MIL-STD 810G standard, thus being shock-resistant. Running Android Nougat, the X venture sports a 5.2-inch Full HD display. Other features of the LG X venture include a 16 MP rear camera with flash, a 5 MP selfie camera, and 32 GB of internal memory. You''re also getting a 4,100 mAh battery, a Snapdragon 435 processor, and 2 GB of RAM.'),
 ('4095', 'LG', 'LG X330', null, 2.3, 156, 109.0, 61.0, 13.8, null, 'Basic phone', null, '320 x  240', 174, 'TFT', 1.3, null, null, 0.08, null, 13.5, 975.0, '2.0', null, 'manufacturer/LG/LG X330.jpg', 'The LG X330 is a candybar phone with QWERTY keyboard dedicated to messaging. It has 2.3" display, 1.3MP camera, FM radio, and Bluetooth.'),
 ('4096', 'LG', 'LG Xenon', null, 2.8, 156, 106.0, 54.0, 16.0, '2009-03-30 00:00:00', null, null, '240 x  400', 167, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.08, 950, 4.0, 264.0, '2.0', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Xenon.jpg', 'LG Xenon offers a sliding form factor with a full QWERTY keyboard, 2 megapixel camera, A-GPS, an accelerometer, and a proximity sensor.'),
 ('4097', 'LG', 'LG Xpression 2', null, 3.0, 156, 108.0, 54.0, 16.0, null, 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  400', 155, 'TFT', 2.0, null, 0.1, 0.063, 1000, 3.75, 390.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Xpression 2.jpg', 'The Xpression 2 is a feature phone that sports 3.0-inch TFT display, single core processor, 128 MB of RAM and 2-megapixels rear shooter. The phone has microSD slot and supports Bluetooth 2.1.'),
 ('4098', 'LG', 'LG Xpression C395', 99, 3.0, 156, 108.0, 54.0, 17.0, null, 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  400', 155, null, 2.0, null, null, 0.05, 1000, 3.0, 240.0, '2.1', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG Xpression C395.jpg', 'The LG Xpression C395 is messaging phone featuring a side sliding QWERTY keyboard, a 3-inch touchscreen display, 2-megapixel camera, Bluetooth and 3G connectivity.'),
 ('4099', 'LG', 'LG dLite', 50, 2.8, 156, 108.0, 52.0, 14.0, '2010-06-02 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  400', 167, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.09, 900, 6.1, 311.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG dLite.jpg', 'LG dLite GD570 is a nice looking GSM clamshell with a hidden LED matrix on the outside of the phone that displays icons for alerts, caller ID, time and date, as well as customizable edge-lit LED light colors and patterns. In addition, the dLite features Social Buzz application that provides easy access to your favorite social networking sites, 3G connectivity and e-mail.'),
 ('4100', 'LG', 'LG eXpo', null, 3.2, 156, 113.0, 55.0, 16.0, '2009-11-30 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Windows Mobile Professional (6.5)', '480 x  800', 292, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.25, null, 1500, 4.0, 408.0, '2.1, EDR', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG eXpo.jpg', 'The LG eXpo GW820 is a business-oriented smartphone, running the Windows Mobile 6.5 operating system. It packs features we do not see very often in cell phones like a detachable pico projector and a fingerprint sensor. The eXpo also sports a 3.2-inch screen and a slide-out QWERTY keyboard.'),
 ('4101', 'LG', 'LG enV Pro', null, 0.0, null, null, null, null, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.2)', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 'Yes', 'A-GPS', '/images/nothumb_phone_235x235.jpg', 'LG enV Pro VS660 will be a CDMA/GSM Hybrid phone running Android. Other features remain unknown.'),
 ('4102', 'LG', 'LG enV Touch', null, 3.0, 156, 115.0, 55.0, 17.0, '2009-05-28 00:00:00', null, null, '480 x  800', 311, 'TFT', 3.2, null, null, null, 950, 4.33, 408.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG enV Touch.jpg', 'The LG enV Touch is the successor of the LG Voyager. Similarly to the previous phone, it is a side-opening clamshell with two large screens, which measure at 3 inches in 480x800 pixels resolution, with the external one being touch-sensitive. Once opened, it has a four-row QWERTY keyboard for handy text messaging. Other features of this really high end phone are a 3.2MP Schneider-Kreuznach camera with flash, document viewer, 3.5mm jack and 1xEV-DO rev.A support.'),
 ('4103', 'LG', 'LG enV2', null, 2.4, 156, 101.6, 54.0, 16.5, '2008-03-31 00:00:00', null, null, '320 x  240', 167, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, null, 950, 5.33, 520.0, '1.2', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG enV2.jpg', 'The VX9100, which will replace the VX9900 enV, has a more streamlined appearance and is slightly thinner, since there is no "camera hump" on the back. The front features a newly designed dialpad with larger buttons than on the enV, as well as replacing the standard 5-way navigational d-pad with more simplistic Up & Down arrow buttons. There still is a small display located at the top. Opening up the VX9100 reveals a better designed QWERTY keypad, along with a standard QVGA display and stereo speakers. Other features include a 2MP Camera, microSD card slot, and microUSB port.'),
 ('4104', 'LG', 'LG enV3', null, 2.6, 156, 104.0, 54.0, 17.0, '2009-05-28 00:00:00', null, null, '320 x  240', 154, 'TFT', 3.0, null, null, null, 950, 5.45, 460.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/LG/LG enV3.jpg', 'The LG enV3 keeps the design language of the enV2, but is a bit slimmer. It also adds a stylish round D-pad and a better external display. Once opened, the enV3 has a larger 2.6-inch main display in the same QVGA resolution. The QWERTY keyboard now has only one Space button. Other features include a 3MP camera with flash and a EV-DO connectivity.'),
