 ('5424', 'Nokia', 'Nokia 8600 Luna', null, 2.0, 156, 107.0, 45.0, 15.9, '2007-05-31 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  320', 200, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.128, 950, 3.7, 240.0, '2.0, EDR', null, 'manufacturer/Nokia/Nokia 8600 Luna.jpg', 'Coming in the class of the 8800, the Nokia 8600 Luna is a high-end phone, using Smoked Glass and Stainless Steel for its construction. The rather unique sliding form-factor reminds of the old 8910 which was replaced by the 8800. Nokia 8600 is a stylish quad-band GSM slider featuring QVGA display, 2 megapixel camera, Bluetooth with A2DP support, Music player, FM Radio and Organizer'),
 ('5425', 'Nokia', 'Nokia 8800 Arte', null, 2.0, 156, 109.0, 45.6, 14.6, '2007-11-13 00:00:00', null, null, '240 x  320', 200, 'OLED', 3.2, null, null, 1.0, 1000, 3.0, 300.0, '2.0, EDR', null, 'manufacturer/Nokia/Nokia 8800 Arte.jpg', 'Nokia 8800 Arte and 8800 Sapphire Arte are two variants of one device - the successor of the 8800 Sirocco. The Arte series improve it with 3G support, QVGA display, 3-megapixel auto-focus camera and 1GB of memory but the functionality is not the most important. Their key feature is the design and the high-class feel thanks to the used materials and unique features like the option to tap on the steel to show a clock or turn the phone with the display facing down to mute an incoming call.\n'),
 ('5426', 'Nokia', 'Nokia 8800 Carbon Arte', null, 2.0, 156, 109.0, 45.6, 14.6, '2008-08-19 00:00:00', null, null, '240 x  320', 200, 'OLED', 3.2, null, null, 4.0, 1000, 3.33, 300.0, '2.0, EDR', null, 'manufacturer/Nokia/Nokia 8800 Carbon Arte.jpg', 'Nokia 8800 Carbon Arte is one of Nokia''s luxury phones. As its name implies, it has pieces of the material (found on both the front and back) in addition to titanium, stainless steel, and polished glass. It is identical to the previous Arte offerings but has 4GB of integrated memory instead of 1GB.'),
 ('5427', 'Nokia', 'Nokia 8800 Gold Arte', null, 2.0, 156, 109.0, 45.6, 14.6, null, null, null, '240 x  320', 200, 'OLED', 3.2, null, null, 4.0, 1000, 3.33, 300.0, '2.0, EDR', null, 'manufacturer/Nokia/Nokia 8800 Gold Arte.jpg', 'Nokia 8800 Gold Arte is the fourth model of the luxury series. It reminds of the Sapphire Arte, as it has leather, but its color is white. Feature-wise, Gold Arte is identical to the Carbon Arte, with 4GB of internal memory.'),
 ('5428', 'Nokia', 'Nokia 8800 Sirocco Edition', null, 0.0, 156, 107.0, 45.0, 16.5, '2006-09-04 00:00:00', null, null, '208 x  208', null, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, 0.128, 700, 2.75, 240.0, '2.0', null, 'manufacturer/Nokia/Nokia 8800 Sirocco Edition.jpg', 'The 8800 Sirocco Edition is a slight upgrade to the original 8800, changing some parts of the design and increasing the memory up to 128MB. The SVGA (800x600) camera is replaced with 2-megapixel one, but the phone still lacks slot for memory and has the same display.'),
 ('5429', 'Nokia', 'Nokia 8801 / 8800', null, 0.0, 156, 107.0, 45.0, 15.0, '2005-03-07 00:00:00', null, null, '208 x  208', null, 'TFT', 0.48, null, null, 0.064, 600, 3.0, 190.0, '1.2', null, 'manufacturer/Nokia/Nokia 8801 _ 8800.jpg', 'Nokia 8801 is a high-end tri-band GSM phone. It features 262k color TFT display, built-in SVGA camera with video capture, Bluetooth, GPRS/EDGE high-speed data, WAP 2.0 Internet browser, Java Midp 2.0 support and MP3/AAC player.'),
