 ('6157', 'Samsung', 'Samsung GALAXY Ace 2', null, 3.8, 156, 118.3, 62.2, 10.5, '2012-02-21 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.1.2, 2.3.6), TouchWiz / L!ve Panel UX UI', '480 x  800', 246, 'Super PLS LCD', 5.0, 0.3, 0.75, 4.0, 1500, 16.33, 670.0, '3.0', 'GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/Samsung/Samsung GALAXY Ace 2.jpg', 'Samsung GALAXY Ace 2 comes to succeed its predecessor with a dual-core 800MHz processor, 5MP camera with HD video recording, 3.8”  WVGA TFT touch screen, Wi-Fi and GPS/Glonass support.'),
 ('6158', 'Samsung', 'Samsung GALAXY Ace DUOS', null, 3.5, 156, 112.74, 61.5, 11.5, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.3)', '320 x  480', 165, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.5, 3.0, 1300, 16.6, 520.0, '3.0', 'A-GPS', 'manufacturer/Samsung/Samsung GALAXY Ace DUOS.jpg', 'The Samsung GALAXY Ace DUOS is a dual-SIM Android device. The version of the OS is 2.3 Gingerbread, and it comes with a 3.5-inch display, 832MHz processor, 5MP camera, 3GB user memory, 512MB RAM and  microSD card slot for up to 32GB.'),
