 ('7752', 'Verizon', 'Verizon Wireless Razzle', null, 2.2, 156, 114.0, 61.0, 13.0, '2009-10-01 00:00:00', null, null, '220 x  176', 128, 'TFT', 1.3, null, null, null, 920, 4.76, 366.0, '2.1', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/Verizon/Verizon Wireless Razzle.jpg', 'Chubby Checker would be very proud of the Verizon Wireless Razzle TXT8030. The device looks like your average candy bar styled handset albeit with an aging feature set that includes a 2.2 inch screen and a 1.3MP camera. There is support for a 16GB microSD card and the handset has a physical QWERTY which is where the fun begins. The bottom half of the model swivels to reveal the QWERTY keyboard and when you''re done sending off that important email or text, you twist the device and a speaker with music controls twists to the front of the phone. A D-pad stays on the same side as the display.'),
