 ('8268', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Avid Plus', 115, 5.0, 156, 144.8, 72.9, 10.9, '2016-01-05 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '480 x  854', 196, 'TFT', 5.0, 2.0, 1.0, 8.0, 2300, 8.0, 350.0, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Avid Plus.jpg', 'Priced at just $115, the ZTE Avid Plus runs Android Lollipop and features a 5-inch, 480 x 854-resolution LCD screen with DragonTrail glass for protection against scratches. Its 5MP rear camera and 2MP front camera may not be particularly impressive, but they certainly do the job of capturing a scene or landing a selfie. The smartphone is powered by a 1.1GHz quad-core Snapdragon processor, paired with 1GB of RAM and 8GB (4GB or less available to the user) of expandable storage. The ZTE Avid Plus is offered exclusively to T-Mobile and MetroPCS subscribers.'),
 ('8269', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Avid Trio', null, 5.0, 156, 144.8, 73.7, 10.2, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '480 x  854', 196, 'LCD', 5.0, 2.0, 1.0, 8.0, 2800, 16.0, 468.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Avid Trio.jpg', 'Тhе ZTE Avid Trio features a 5-inch FWVGA display, 1.4GHz quad-core display, 1GB of RAM and 8 gigs of expandable internal storage. The phone is LTE enabled and runs Android 6.0.  There is a 5-megapixel main shooter on the back, as well as a 2-megapixel front camera for selfies.'),
 ('8270', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon 7 Max', 440, 6.0, 156, 157.0, 80.4, 8.2, '2016-10-27 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0), MiFavor UI', '1080 x  1920', 367, null, 13.0, 13.0, 4.0, 64.0, 4100, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon 7 Max.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon 7 Max is not stuffed to the gills with top-shelf specs, but rather boasts a 6" 1080p panel, 2.0 GHz octa-core Snapdragon 625 chipset, 4 GB of RAM, 64 GB of storage plus a microSD card, and a 4100 mAh battery. The phone boasts a dual rear camera setup with two 13 MP units (one for depth of field) that take advantage of a laser autofocusing system. That''s not the only arrow in its multimedia quiver, though, as it also has a dedicated AK4962 hi-res audio chip, and a "Naked 3D" display layer that lets you watch 3D content without special glasses.'),
 ('8271', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon 7 Mini', 299, 5.2, 156, 147.5, 71.0, 7.8, '2016-09-01 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.1, 6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'AMOLED', 16.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 2705, 15.0, 270.0, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass, BeiDou', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon 7 Mini.jpg', 'The Axon 7 Mini is a mid-range smartphone and like the Axon Mini from last year, the new handset offers a 5.2-inch 1080p AMOLED display, which doesn''t really make it a mini phone. Made out of metal, the ZTE Axon 7 Mini is powered by an octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 617 processor, and runs Android 6.0 Marshmallow. Other features include LTE, dual SIM support, 3 GB of RAM, 32 GB of expandable storage space, and a 2705 mAh battery. On the back, the new Axon has a fingerprint scanner and a 16 MP camera, while its front-facing camera is an 8 MP one.'),
 ('8272', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon 7', 400, 5.5, 156, 151.7, 75.0, 7.9, '2016-05-26 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.1, 6.0), MiFavor UI', '1440 x  2560', 534, 'AMOLED', 20.0, 8.0, 4.0, 64.0, 3250, null, null, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon 7.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon 7 is spec''d out beyond compromise. Featuring a 5.5-inch, Quad-HD AMOLED screen, the Android 6.0.1-running device is powered by Qualcomm''s premium-tier Snapdragon 820 chip, paired with either 4GB RAM and 64GB of storage, or a whopping 6GB of RAM and 128GB of memory. The smartphone is equipped with an USB 3.0 Type-C port for fast data transfer and convenient plugging in and out. It is also among the first devices to support ''Daydream'', Google''s mobile virtual reality engine. Moving to the camera setup, a 20MP main camera with a Samsung ISOCELL sensor and an 8MP front cam will face your photography needs.The rear camera comes with a plethora of extras, including OIS+, EIS+, PDAF, a wide F/1.8 aperture, and a dual-LED flash. It can also record 30FPS videos in up to 4K resolution, along with 720p resolution/240FPS slow motion reels.'),
 ('8273', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon 8', null, 5.5, null, null, null, null, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android', '1440 x  2560', 534, null, 12.0, 8.0, 4.0, 128.0, null, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon 8.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon 8 is expected to feature a 5.5-inch QHD display that has 2560 x 1440 pixels resolution. Under the hood, the phone will have Qualcomm Snapdragon 820 2.1 GHz quad-core processor, 4GB RAM and 128GB of internal storage. A 12-megapixel autofocus camera and a LED flash is expected on phones rear panel.'),
 ('8274', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon Elite', null, 5.5, null, 154.0, 75.0, 9.3, '2015-09-04 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0), MiFavor 3.2 UI', '1080 x  1920', 401, 'LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 3000, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass, BeiDou', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon Elite.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon Elite is yet another variation of the ZTE Axon, which employs the distinguishable design of the latter. Apart from a 5.5-inch 1080p display, a Snapdragon 810, 3GB of RAM, 32GB storage + microSD card slot, and a 3,000mAh battery, the Axon Elite is also adorned with several biometric sensors. These allow you to unlock the phone with your fingerprint, with your voice, or by getting your retina scanned.'),
 ('8275', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon Lux', 450, 5.5, 156, 154.5, 75.3, 9.7, '2015-07-21 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '1440 x  2560', 534, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 4.0, 128.0, 3000, 12.0, 240.0, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon Lux.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon Lux sports a 5.5-inch Sharp-made TFT Quad HD (1440 x 2560 pixels) display, and runs a near-stock version of Android 5.1.1 Lollipop. Powered by an octa-core Snapdragon 810 processor, the Axon Lux further offers LTE connectivity, 4 GB of RAM, 128 GB of storage space, and a 3000 mAh non-removable battery. The rear camera of the Axon Pro is a dual-lens one (13 MP + 2 MP, suitable for bokeh effects) with 4K video recording and f/1.8 aperture, while the front-facing camera is an 8 MP one. A highlight of the ZTE Axon Lux - "the world’s first smartphone that can be unlocked with three different biometric authentication options".'),
 ('8276', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon Max 2', null, 6.0, null, null, null, null, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 367, null, 13.0, 13.0, 4.0, 64.0, null, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', '/images/nothumb_phone_235x235.jpg', 'With the ZTE Axon Max 2, it looks like ZTE will seek to refine the experience from the Axon Max, rather than chase an all-out specs bump. The ZTE Axon Max 2 will retain a 6-inch, 1080p display, while both front and back cameras may pack 13-megapixel resolutions. The marquee enhancement may take the form of Qualcomm''s Snapdragon 625, a powerful yet power-efficient chip that should get the job done during most everyday activities.'),
 ('8277', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon Max', null, 6.0, null, 160.0, 80.0, 7.5, '2015-12-18 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1), MiFavor UI', '1080 x  1920', 367, 'AMOLED', 16.0, 13.0, 3.0, 32.0, 4140, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass, BeiDou', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon Max.jpg', 'Running Android 5.1 Lollipop, the Axon Max seems to be built around a metal frame. The smartphone features LTE connectivity, dual SIM support, 3 GB of RAM, 32 GB of internal memory, microSD card support, and a generous 4140 mAh battery. The front camera of the Axon Max is a 13 MP one, while a 16 MP camera sits on the back alongside a fingerprint scanner.'),
 ('8278', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon Mini', null, 5.2, 156, 143.5, 70.0, 7.9, '2015-07-21 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1), MiFavor 3.2 UI', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'AMOLED', 13.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 2800, 18.0, 400.0, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon Mini.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon Mini is equipped with a 5.2-inch OLED display carrying a resolution of 1080 x 1920. That works out to a 424 ppi pixel density. An octa-core 1.5GHz CPU is under the hood with 3GB of RAM inside. 32GB of internal storage is on board, and those seeking more can turn to the 128GB capacity microSD slot. The rear-facing camera is 13MP, and the front-facing camera is 8MP.  The unit does support 4G LTE connectivity and Android 5.1.1 is pre-installed. The Axon Mini is 7.9mm thin and weighs in at 140 grams.'),
 ('8279', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon Pro', 500, 5.5, 156, 154.0, 75.0, 9.3, '2015-07-14 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0, 5.1)', '1440 x  2560', 534, 'TFT', 13.0, 8.0, 4.0, 64.0, 3000, 12.0, 240.0, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon Pro.jpg', 'Made out of materials like metal and glass, the ZTE Axon Pro measures 154 x 75 x 9.3 mm and weighs 173 grams, so it''s not the thinnest, nor the lightest high-end smartphone on the market. The new handset sports a 5.5-inch Sharp-made TFT Quad HD (1440 x 2560 pixels) display, and runs a near-stock version of Android 5.1.1 Lollipop. Powered by an octa-core Snapdragon 810 processor, the Axon Pro further offers LTE connectivity, 4 GB of RAM, 32 GB of storage space (apparently not expandable), and a 3000 mAh non-removable battery. The rear camera of the Axon Pro is a dual-lens one (13 MP + 2 MP, suitable for bokeh effects) with 4K video recording and f/1.8 aperture, while the front-facing camera is an 8 MP one. A highlight of the ZTE Axon Pro - at least according to ZTE - is that it features an AKM 4961 Hi-Fi (high fidelity) audio chipset that should deliver "excellent sound quality."'),
 ('8280', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon tablet', null, 13.7, null, null, null, null, null, 'Tablet', 'Android (5.0)', '1920 x  1080', 161, null, 2.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, null, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', '/images/nothumb_phone_235x235.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon tablet is expected to feature a 13.7-inch screen, with a resolution of 1080 x 1920. That works out to a pixel density of 160ppi. Qualcomm''s current high-end chipset, the Snapdragon 810, is under the hood, carrying a slightly under-clocked octa-core 1.9GHz CPU. The Adreno 430 GPU handles graphics. 3GB of RAM is inside, along with 32GB of internal storage. Those requiring additional memory can access the 128GB capacity microSD slot that is on board. A 8MP snapper adorns the front of the slate, with a 2MP camera found on the back. Android 5.0.2 is pre-installed. The tablet supports 4G LTE, and is NFC enabled.'),
 ('8281', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Axon', 330, 5.5, 156, 153.9, 73.7, 9.4, '2015-07-14 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '1080 x  1920', 401, 'TFT', 13.0, 8.0, 2.0, 32.0, 3000, 25.0, 300.0, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Axon.jpg', 'The ZTE Axon sports a 5.5-inch Sharp-made TFT 1080p display, and runs a near-stock version of Android 5.1.1 Lollipop. Powered by an quad-core Snapdragon 801 processor, the Axon further offers LTE connectivity, 2 GB of RAM, 32 GB of storage space (not expandable), and a 3000 mAh non-removable battery. The rear camera of the Axon Pro is a dual-lens one (13 MP + 2 MP, suitable for bokeh effects) with 4K video recording and f/1.8 aperture, while the front-facing camera is an 8 MP one.'),
 ('8282', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade C', null, 4.0, null, 124.0, 64.0, 11.0, '2013-01-29 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.1)', '480 x  800', 233, null, 3.0, null, 0.5, 4.0, 1600, null, null, '4.0', null, 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade C.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade C is a budget smartphone. It comes with Android 4.1 Jelly Bean right out of the box. Specs-wise, the ZTE Blade C treats you to a 4" WVGA display, 3MP camera, 1GHz dual-core MediaTek MTK 6577 processor, 512MB RAM and 4GB of internal memory.'),
 ('8283', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade III', null, 4.0, 156, 120.5, 63.5, 10.85, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0)', '480 x  800', 233, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 0.5, 4.0, 1650, 4.0, 250.0, 'Yes', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade III.jpg', 'ZTE Blade III is an Android smartphone with 1GHz processor, 512MB ram, 4GB of internal memory and 5MP camera.'),
 ('8284', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade II', null, 3.5, 156, 115.1, 57.9, 10.9, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.0, 2.3)', '480 x  800', 267, 'TFT', 5.0, 0.3, 0.5, 0.2, 1200, null, null, '2.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade II.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade II is an Android 2.3 smartphone with a 3.5-inch touchscreen, 5-megapixel autofocus camera, Wi-Fi, GPS, FM radio and organizer.'),
 ('8285', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade Max 3', null, 6.0, 156, 164.8, 84.1, 8.9, '2017-04-25 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 367, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 4000, 40.0, 744.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade Max 3.jpg', 'Powered by an octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 625 processor, the ZTE Blade Max 3 sports a 6-inch display with 1080 x 1920 pixels, and packs a 4,000 mAh battery - good enough for a talk time of up to 40 hours, or a stand-by time of up to 31 days. The handset further offers a fingerprint scanner, a 13 MP dual rear camera, 5 MP front-facing camera, and a USB Type C port.'),
 ('8286', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade Q Mini', null, 4.0, null, 125.0, 64.0, 9.0, '2013-10-31 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.2)', '480 x  800', 233, 'IPS LCD', 5.0, null, 1.0, 4.0, 1500, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade Q Mini.jpg', 'Blade Q Mini has a 4-inch low resolution display (480 x 800), 1.2 GHz dual-core processor and 5-megapixel camera with autofocus.'),
 ('8287', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade S6 Plus', 277, 5.5, 156, 155.0, 78.0, 7.7, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0), MiFavor 3.0 UI', '720 x  1280', 267, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 3000, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade S6 Plus.jpg', 'ZTE Blade S6 Plus runs Android 5.0 Lollipop, and is powered by a 64-bit, octa-core Snapdragon 615 processor. The display is 5.5-inch IPS one with 720 x 1280 pixels resolution. Its other features include LTE, dual SIM capabilities, a 5 MP front-facing camera, 13 MP rear camera, 2 GB of RAM, and 16 GB of expandable storage space.'),
 ('8288', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade S6', 250, 5.0, 156, 144.0, 70.7, 7.7, '2015-01-28 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0),  MiFavor 3.0 UI', '720 x  1280', 294, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2400, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade S6.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade S6 flaunts a 5" laminated HD display, an octa-core 64-bit Snapdragon 615 chipset, 2 GB of RAM, 16 GB of internal storage plus microSD slot, and a 13 MP rear camera plus a 5 MP wide-angle front cam. All of it is backed by a 2400 mAh battery pack, and is running the latest Android 5.0 Lollipop.'),
 ('8289', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade Spark', 99, 5.5, 156, 156.0, 77.7, 9.7, '2017-07-14 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0)', '720 x  1280', 267, null, 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 3140, null, null, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade Spark.jpg', 'With its rather light price-tag, the Blade Spark''s specs are justifiably low-tier - a quad-core, 1.4 GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon 425 SoC, 2 GB of RAM, and 16 GB of storage expandable via microSD. The display is rather large, with a 5.5-inch diagonal, but not extremely sharp, with a 720 x 1280 pixel resolution. The cameras sound good on paper, with a 13 MP PDAF-assisted sensor at the back and a 5 MP snapper on the fron. There''s an included fingerprint scanner on the back. Considering it''s a phone that''s best meant for light usage, its 3,140 mAh battery seems quite generous and will probably last you a while. The Blade Spark comes with Android 7.1.1 Nougat out of the box.'),
 ('8290', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade V6', 249, 5.0, 156, 142.0, 69.5, 6.8, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0), MiFavor 3.0 UI', '720 x  1280', 294, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2200, 7.0, 440.0, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade V6.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade V6 is a dual-SIM, aluminum beauty measuring only 6.9 mm in thickness. The Blade V6 features 5-inch 720p display, MediaTek MT6735 SOC accompanied with 2GB of RAM and 16 gigs of internal, expandable storage. There is a 13-megapixel camera on the back, as well as a 5-megapixel selfie unit. The phone is powered by 2200 mAh battery and runs Android 5.0.'),
 ('8291', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade V7 Lite', null, 5.0, 156, 143.8, 70.2, 7.9, '2016-02-22 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '720 x  1280', 294, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2500, 8.0, 150.0, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade V7 Lite.jpg', 'Being a Lite version, this one is smaller than the Blade V7 and has a 720p resolution, 5-inch display. Designed in Germany and also metallic, the handset features a circular fingerprint scanner for biometric security. Like its bigger brother, the V7 Lite runs Android 6.0, but it opts for a quad-core MediaTek chipset. It still has 2GB of RAM and 16GB of expandable storage, along with 8MP front and rear cameras – both with flash modules.'),
 ('8292', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade V7', null, 5.2, null, 146.0, 72.5, 7.5, '2016-02-22 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2500, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade V7.jpg', 'Boasting a full-metal body, the Blade V7 flaunts a 1080p-resolution, 5.2-inch screen that''s topped off with curved edge glass. The smartphones is powered by an octa-core MediaTek chip with 2GB of RAM and 16GB of storage. The Blade V7 runs the latest Android 6.0 Marshmallow, which is commendable and makes for one up-to-date device. There''s a 13MP camera with quick phase-detection autofocus and dual-tone LED flash on the rear, along with a 5MP cam on the front, while the battery is of 2500mAh capacity.'),
 ('8293', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade V8 Lite', null, 5.0, 156, null, null, null, '2017-02-27 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0), MiFavor UI', '1080 x  1920', 441, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2500, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade V8 Lite.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade V8 comes with a 5-inch 1080p display, 1.5 GHz MediaTek octa-core processor, 2 GB of RAM, 16 GB of storage, an 13-megapixel autofocus main camera, a 8-megapixel selfie unit and a fingerprint sensor.'),
 ('8294', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade V8 Mini', null, 5.0, 156, 143.5, 70.0, 8.9, '2017-02-27 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0), MiFavor UI', '720 x  1280', 294, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2800, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade V8 Mini.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade V8 Mini is a 5-inch Android smartphone powered by Snapdragon 430 SOC and 2GB of RAM. 16GB internal memory and microSD slot are available for storage. There is a 13-megapixels dual-camera on the back, as well as a 2-megapixels front shooter with flash. The phone runs Android 7.0 Nougat.'),
 ('8295', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade V8 Pro', 230, 5.5, 156, 156.0, 77.0, 9.1, '2017-01-04 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1080 x  1920', 401, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 3140, 24.0, 552.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade V8 Pro.jpg', 'The Blade V8 Pro is a mid-range handset at heart, as the phone is powered by an octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 625 processor, coupled with 3GB of RAM and 32GB of internal memory (expandable up to 128GB via microSD). It''s worth noting that the phone features hybrid dual-SIM support, so you can either use two SIM cards, or one SIM card and a memory card. The physical Home button hides a fingerprint sensor. ZTE Blade V8 Pro sports a 5.5-inch display that supports full HD (1080p) resolution and Corning Gorilla Glass 3 coating. The phone is powered by a 3,140 mAh battery that features Quick Charge 2.0 support.'),
 ('8296', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade V8', null, 5.2, 156, 148.4, 71.5, 7.7, '2017-01-05 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.0)', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 13.0, 3.0, 32.0, 2730, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade V8.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade V8 has a dual-camera setup where a main 13MP camera is paired with a 2MP secondary cam, on the back. This allows various effects to be applied to the image, including background blur (a.k.a. bokeh).  Another feature being highlighted is the V8''s ability to take 3D photos. The phone can''t display glasses-free 3D, mind you, and we''re not really sure what these 3D images will look like. Camera aside, the ZTE Blade V8 has mid-range written all over it. Specs include a Snapdragon 435 chip, a 5.2-inch Full HD display, a 2730mAh battery, a fingerprint sensor, and LTE support across a multitude of bands. Also, the phone will come in two configurations: one with 2GB of RAM and 16 GB of storage, and another sporting 3GB of RAM and 32GB of storage.'),
 ('8297', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade Vec 3G', 180, 5.0, null, 139.3, 69.8, 7.8, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4)', '720 x  1280', 294, 'LCD', 8.0, 5.0, 1.0, 8.0, 2300, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade Vec 3G.jpg', 'The ZTE Blade Vec 3G runs Android 4.4 KitKat and is powered by a 1.3GHz quad-core Cortex-A7 processor with 1GB RAM. Storage is 8 GB, expandable through microSD card slot. It has a 5" 720p display, 8MP main camera and a 5MP front-facing camera.'),
 ('8298', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade Vec 4G', 230, 5.0, 156, 142.3, 70.4, 7.8, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4.2)', '720 x  1280', 294, 'IPS LCD', 8.0, 1.0, 1.0, 16.0, 2300, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade Vec 4G.jpg', 'The Blade Vec 4G is an Android 4.4-based phone, powered by a Snapdragon 400 chipset with 1.2GHz quad Cortex-A7 processor and 1GB RAM. The 16 GB storage can be further expanded via microSD slot. It comes in two variants - with an 8MP or a 13MP camera (region dependant) and a 1MP or 2MP front-facing camera. The Blade Vec 4G is equipped with a 5" display with 720 x 1280 pixels resolution.'),
 ('8299', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade X Max', 149, 6.0, 156, 165.1, 83.1, 9.4, '2017-05-11 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.1)', '1080 x  1920', 367, 'TFT', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 32.0, 3400, 17.7, 241.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade X Max.jpg', 'The Blade X Max sports a huge, 6-inch full HD display, which, combined with its 3,400 mAh battery and low-power Qualcomm Snapdragon 435 SoC, promises a considerable battery life, which ZTE claims can reach up to 17.7 hours of talk time and a whopping 241 hours in standby mode. The device also sports 2 GB of RAM, as well as 32 GB of internal storage, though the latter can be expanded via SD card.'),
 ('8300', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade Z Max', 129, 6.0, 156, 166.1, 84.6, 8.4, '2017-08-14 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (7.1)', '1080 x  1920', 367, 'IPS LCD', 16.0, 8.0, 2.0, 32.0, 4080, 31.0, 528.0, '4.2', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade Z Max.jpg', 'Just like the Zmax Pro, the Blade X Max offers a rear-facing fingerprint scanner. What''s new here actually sits right above it: this is the latest device to jump on the dual camera bandwagon, sporting a weird combo of a primary 16 MP sensor, and a secondary 2 MP one, though the latter will be used primarily for the obligatory portrait mode. The front camera is also upgraded, and now produces images with an 8 MP resolution. Inside you''ll find some pretty modest specs: a Qualcomm Snapdragon 435 chipset with 2 gigs of RAM and 32 GB of storage (expandable via SD card). There is, however, one particularly impressive aspect to the device: the large 4,080 mAh battery.'),
 ('8301', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Blade', null, 3.5, 156, 116.0, 56.5, 11.8, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (2.1)', '480 x  800', 267, null, 3.0, null, null, 0.15, null, 4.0, 216.0, '2.1, EDR', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Blade.jpg', 'ZTE Blade also known as Orange San Francisco is an Android 2.1 running smartphone with 3.5" touchscreen. It has 3MP camera, Wi-Fi, GPS, FM radio and 600 MHz processor.'),
 ('8302', 'ZTE', 'ZTE C78', null, 2.0, 156, 109.0, 48.0, 14.0, null, null, null, '176 x  220', 141, 'TFT', 0.3, null, null, 0.06, 900, 3.5, 180.0, '2.0', null, 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE C78.jpg', 'ZTE C78 is a simple CDMA candybar, featuring 262k color TFT display, VGA camera, MP3 player and stereo Bluetooth.'),
 ('8303', 'ZTE', 'ZTE C79', null, 0.0, null, 89.0, 44.0, 17.0, null, null, null, '176 x  220', null, 'TFT', 1.3, null, null, 0.069, 1000, 3.6, 200.0, '2.0', null, 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE C79.jpg', 'ZTE C79 is a basic CDMA clamshell featuring dual color displays, 1.3MP Camera, Stereo Bluetooth, Phonebook and Organizer.'),
 ('8304', 'ZTE', 'ZTE C88', null, 2.0, 156, 98.0, 48.0, 17.0, null, null, null, '176 x  220', 141, 'TFT', 0.3, null, null, 0.06, 800, 3.5, 120.0, '1.1', 'E911', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE C88.jpg', 'ZTE C88 is a basic CDMA clamshell featuring dual color displays, Camera, Bluetooth, Phonebook and Organizer.'),
 ('8305', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Chorus', 80, 3.2, 156, 112.0, 56.0, 15.0, '2011-11-23 00:00:00', 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  400', 146, 'TFT', 2.0, null, null, null, 1000, 4.16, 220.0, 'Yes', 'GPS, E911', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Chorus.jpg', 'The ZTE Chorus is an entry level music centric device available from Cricket. The phone sports a 3.2-inch resistive touch WQVGA display, 2-megapixel camera, multimedia players, GPS, organizer and 3G connectivity.'),
 ('8306', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Compel', null, 4.0, 156, 125.0, 65.0, 11.4, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4.2)', '480 x  800', 233, 'TFT', 5.0, null, 1.0, 4.0, 1820, 4.5, 360.0, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Compel.jpg', 'The ZTE Compel is a smartphone with Android 4.4.2 out of the box. It offers a 4" display, 1.2 GHz quad core Snapdragon 400 processor coupled with 1 GB RAM, 4 GB of storage, expandable through a microSD slot, and a 5 MP rear camera.'),
 ('8307', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Coral200 Sollar', null, 1.5, 156, 106.0, 45.6, 18.1, null, 'Basic phone', null, '128 x  128', 121, 'STN', null, null, null, null, null, 5.5, 180.0, null, null, 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Coral200 Sollar.jpg', 'The ZTE Colar200 Sollar is a solar powered candybar phone with a 1.5-inch color display, messaging, 2 games and  polyphonic ringtones.'),
 ('8308', 'ZTE', 'ZTE Cymbal Z-320', null, 2.8, 156, 104.1, 55.9, 17.8, null, 'Feature phone', null, '240 x  320', 143, 'LCD', 2.0, null, 0.5, 4.0, 1500, 13.5, 504.0, '4.0', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/ZTE/ZTE Cymbal Z-320.jpg', 'ZTE Cymbal Z-320 is a feature phone that sports a 2.8-inch display, Snapdragon 210 SOC with 512MB RAM and 4 gigs of expandable storage. The phone is LTE enabled and is powered by 1500mAh battery.'),
