 ('8749', 'nubia', 'nubia W5', null, 0.0, null, null, null, null, null, 'Smart phone', 'Windows Phone, 8.1', null, null, null, 13.0, null, 3.0, 64.0, 4500, null, null, 'Yes', 'GPS', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia W5.jpg', 'ZTE Nubia W5 is said to be a high-end Windows Phone flavored device with the Snapdragon 801 chip under the hood, 3GB of RAM and 64GB of native storage on board. The rear-facing camera is expected to be 13MP and features OIS. This phone would offer 4G connectivity and it would be all powered up by a massive 4500mAh battery.'),
 ('8750', 'nubia', 'nubia X6', null, 6.4, 156, 179.5, 89.0, 7.9, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4)', '1080 x  1920', 342, null, 13.0, 13.0, 3.0, 32.0, 4250, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia X6.jpg', 'Apart from the 6.44-inch 1080p display, the ZTE Nubia X6 device features a quad-core Snapdragon 801 chipset clocked at 2.3GHz, 3GB RAM, and a special pair of cameras – a 13MP rear camera with f/2.0 aperture, 5-element lens and OIS, and a 13MP front-facing camera with backside illumination and f/2.2 aperture size. Additionally, the phablet has a dual-SIM slot, 3G and LTE network support, dual-band Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, NFC, and three noise-canceling mics for calls and recordings. The monster of a phablet is powered by a 4250mAh battery.'),
 ('8751', 'nubia', 'nubia Z11 Max', null, 6.0, 156, 159.15, 82.25, 7.4, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '1080 x  1920', 367, 'Super AMOLED', 16.0, 8.0, 4.0, 64.0, 4000, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z11 Max.jpg', 'The ZTE Nubia Z11 Max comes with a 6-inch 1080p screen, octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 652 chip, 4 GB of RAM, 64 GB of storage, 16-megapixel main camera and and additional 8-megapixel selfie unit on the front.'),
 ('8752', 'nubia', 'nubia Z11 Mini', null, 5.0, 156, 141.4, 70.0, 8.0, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1)', '1080 x  1920', 441, 'IPS LCD', 16.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 2800, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z11 Mini.jpg', 'The ZTE Nubia Z11 Mini comes with a 5-inch 1080p IPS display, octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 617 chip, 3 GB of RAM, 64 GB of storage, 16-megapixel main camera and an additional 8-megapixel selfie unit on the front.'),
 ('8753', 'nubia', 'nubia Z11', null, 5.5, 156, 151.8, 72.3, 7.7, '2016-06-29 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (6.0)', '1920 x  1080', 402, 'TFT', 16.0, 8.0, 6.0, 64.0, 3000, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z11.jpg', 'The ZTE Nubia Z11 comes with a 5.5-inch 1080p display, quad-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 820 chip, 6 GB of RAM (there is also a 4GB version), 64/128 GB of storage which is further expandable via microSD card, a 16-megapixel OIS rear facing camera and an additional 8-megapixel selfie unit on the front.'),
 ('8754', 'nubia', 'nubia Z5S', null, 5.0, 156, 137.7, 68.8, 7.6, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.2.2)', '1080 x  1920', 441, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2300, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z5S.jpg', 'The ZTE nubia Z5S is an Android-based smartphone, with a five-inch Sharp 1080p FHD display, a 13 MP camera with a Sony RS sensor, F2.0 aperture, DSLR-like photo options, and 4K Ultra HD video capture. Not much more info is available at the moment.'),
 ('8755', 'nubia', 'nubia Z7 Max', null, 5.5, 156, null, null, null, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.1, 4.4.2), Nubia 2.0 UI', '1080 x  1920', 401, null, 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 32.0, 3100, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z7 Max.jpg', 'Contrary to its name, the ZTE nubia Z7 Max also has a 5.5" display panel, but it comes with 1080p resolution. The overall size grows, however, to 152.7 x 76 x 8.7mm. There are also 2 GB of RAM, instead of 3 GB, and these seem to sum up the difference between the Z7, and its cheaper Max variation.'),
 ('8756', 'nubia', 'nubia Z7 mini', null, 5.0, 156, 140.9, 69.3, 8.2, '2014-07-08 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4.2), Nubia 2.5 UI', '1080 x  1920', 441, null, 13.0, 2.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2300, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z7 mini.jpg', 'The ZTE nubia Z7 mini sports a 5-inch 1080p display, 13 megapixel shooter with flash and two SIM card slots. The device is powered by Qualcomm Snapdragon 801 chip featuring a 2GHz quad core processor and 2GB of RAM. The available storage space equates to 16GB and is expandable via a microSD card slot.'),
 ('8757', 'nubia', 'nubia Z7', null, 5.5, null, 153.2, 75.7, 8.9, '2014-07-08 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4.2), ZTE Nubia 2.5 UI', '1440 x  2560', 534, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 3.0, 32.0, 3000, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z7.jpg', 'The ZTE nubia Z7 has 5.5" Quad HD screen with the splendid 1440x2560 pixels of resolution, quad-core Snapdragon 801 processor, 3 GB of RAM, 32 GB of storage, 13 MP camera with optical image stabilization on the back, 3000 mAh battery, and 4G LTE connectivity. As you can expect, it is also a dual SIM LTE device.'),
 ('8758', 'nubia', 'nubia Z9 Max', 400, 5.5, 156, 154.8, 76.6, 7.9, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0), nubia 2.8 UI', '1080 x  1920', 401, 'IPS LCD', 16.0, 8.0, 3.0, 16.0, 2900, null, null, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z9 Max.jpg', 'The Nubia Z9 Max is an impressive piece of hardware. It comes in a beautiful, 0.31 inches (7.9 mm) body made out of aircraft grade aluminum and glass, with an attractive pattern on the back. Both the rear and the 5.5-inch, 1080 x 1920 pixel resolution Sharp screen are protected by a sheet of Gorilla Glass 3, further adding to the offering. On the inside, the Nubia Z9 Max sports an octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 810 processor with an Adreno 430 GPU, 3GB of super-fast LPDDR4 RAM, 16GB of expandable storage, and two nano-SIM slots. The pride of the Nubia Z9 Max is its camera, though, just like with all previous Nubia device. Indeed, the Z9 Max is just as camera-centric as its predecessors, and brings a 16-megapixel, 1/2.6" Sony IMX234 Exmor RS sensor to the table with 6 element, f/2.0 lens and support for 4K UHD video capture. Up front, we''ve got a wide-angled, 8-megapixel Sony IMX179 Exmor R sensor with 1.4μm pixels and f/2.4 aperture.'),
 ('8759', 'nubia', 'nubia Z9 mini', 299, 5.0, 156, 141.3, 69.8, 8.2, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0), nubia 2.8 UI', '1080 x  1920', 441, 'IPS LCD', 16.0, 8.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2900, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z9 mini.jpg', 'The Nubia Z9 mini a 5" 1080p screen, Snapdragon 615 chipset, 2 GB RAM, 16 GB of storage plus an expansion slot, but the same 16 MP and 8 MP camera combo like on the big brother. This one sports a titanium frame in its turn, too, and is powered by the same 2900 mAh battery pack.'),
 ('8760', 'nubia', 'nubia Z9', null, 5.2, 156, 147.4, 68.3, 8.9, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0), nubia 3.0 UI', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'IPS LCD', 16.0, 8.0, 3.0, 32.0, 2900, null, 72.0, '4.1', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/nubia/nubia Z9.jpg', 'The Nubia Z9 offers features like a 5.2-inch 1080p display, an octa-core Snapdragon 810 processor, 16 MP rear camera, 8 MP front-facing camera, and a 2900 mAh battery. The handset runs Android Lollipop customized with ZTE''s Nubia 3.0 UI.'),
 ('8761', 'vivo', 'vivo X5 Max', null, 5.5, 156, 153.9, 78.0, 4.8, '2014-12-10 00:00:00', 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.4.4), Funtouch 2.0 UI', '1080 x  1920', 401, 'Super AMOLED', 13.0, 5.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2300, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/vivo/vivo X5 Max.jpg', 'Chinese manufacturer Vivo officially announced the Vivo X5 Max, an uber-thin smartphone that measures just 0.15in (3.98mm) at its thinnest point and 0.18in (4.75mm) at its chubbiest. In terms of specs the phone offers a 5.5-inch 1080p Super-AMOLED screen and runs on a Qualcomm Snapdragon 615 1.7GHz octa-core processor, paired with 2GB of RAM and 16GB of expandable storage. A 13MP rear camera and a 5MP front cam take care of photos, while an Yamaha YSS-205X chip handles sound. The Vivo X5 Max runs Android 4.4.4 KitKat topped off with Funtouch OS 2.0.'),
 ('8762', 'vivo', 'vivo X5Pro', null, 5.2, 156, 147.9, 73.45, 6.39, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (5.0), Funtouch OS UI', '1080 x  1920', 424, 'Super AMOLED', 13.0, 8.0, 2.0, 16.0, 2450, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS, Glonass', 'manufacturer/vivo/vivo X5Pro.jpg', 'The vivo X5Pro is a powerful smartphone with Android 5.0. Its specs include 5.2" 1080p display, 1.5 GHz octa-core CPU, 2 GB RAM, 16 GB ROM, microSD card slot for up to 128 GB extra storage, 13 MP rear camera with Sapphire crystal lens cover, and a 8 MP front one for video calls. Dual SIM card support is also present.'),
 ('8763', 'vivo', 'vivo Xplay 3S', null, 6.0, 156, 158.2, 82.59, 8.68, null, 'Smart phone', 'Android (4.3)', '1440 x  2560', 490, 'IPS LCD', 13.0, 5.0, 3.0, 32.0, 3200, null, null, '4.0', 'GPS, A-GPS', 'manufacturer/vivo/vivo Xplay 3S.jpg', 'The Vivo XPlay 3S is the world’s first smartphone with a 2560 x 1440 pixel 6 inch screen. It is powered by a 2.3GHz Snapdragon 800 processor and has 3GB of RAM and 32 GS storage space. Other features include a 13-megapixel camera with an f/1.8 aperture, and 4G LTE connectivity.');
